  <titleInfo>
    <title>[Letter] 1797 Feb. 7, Knoxville, Tennessee [to] Captains Sparks &amp; Wade / John Sevier</title>
  </titleInfo>
  <abstract>This document is a brief letter from governor John Sevier of Tennessee to Captains Sparks and Wade. The purpose of the letter is to instruct them to assist and console and offer favorable indulgences to the unfortunate plight of the Indians targeted for removal from their land to West of the Mississippi river.</abstract>
